==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miscellany
<hw>Mis"cel*la*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Miscellanies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>miscellanea</ets>, neut. pl. of. <ets>miscellaneus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>miscellan⟦eacute⟧e</ets>, pl. <ets>miscellan⟦eacute⟧es</ets>. See
<er>Miscellaneous</er>.]</ety> <def>A mass or mixture of various things;
a medley; esp., a collection of compositions on various
subjects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is but a bundle or <qex>miscellany</qex> of sin; sins original,
and sins actual.</q> <rj><qau>Hewyt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Miscellany madam</b></col>, <cd>a woman who dealt in
various fineries; a milliner.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B.
Jonson.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 929 --></p>

